<L>__{interior tim's living room moments later}
<A>__{tim opens the door to millie vanderhei, 54, a thick, depressive woman dressed like a 7th grade science teacher.}
<C>__{tim}
<D>__{there she is! how you feeling?}
<C>__{millie}
<D>__{oh, it's no big whoop.}
<A>__{tim pulls the card and beanie baby duck from behind his back.}
<C>__{tim}
<D>__{ta da.}
<P>__{(re. the stuffed duck)}
<D>__{quack, quack. d'you already have this guy? wasn't sure.}
<C>__{millie}
<D>__{gayle syrstad gave me a quackers for secret santa last year. i can probably trade with nan, though.}
<A>__{millie sits on tim's paisley sofa. she opens the card. on the front: a rottweiler in a nurse's outfit. inside: "get well or you deal with me!" then in tim's writing, "love, tim."}
<C>__{millie }
<P>__{(chuckles at the card)}
<D>__{cute. brandy would never sit still long enough for me to dress her up like that. tell you that right now.}
<P>__{(then)}
<D>__{you didn't have to do this whole rigmarole, tim. i told you it's just a little diarrhea.}
<C>__{tim}
<D>__{i know. but for you to miss a day of school, millie... i can't remember you ever calling in sick when i had you.}
<C>__{millie}
<D>__{well i wasn't going through menopause when you were in middle school now was i?}
<C>__{tim}
<D>__{negative. not to my knowledge. not to my knowledge.}
<A>__{she nods somberly. they sit there silently for a bit. then:}
